name: Buck Melanoma
snippet: Solid steaks and great variety, you can never really go wrong here. We had one small steak and one larger, great garlic mash, shrimp and bacon wrapped scallops on a skewer. Intimate but comfortable atmosphere. A little pricier but worth every bit in quality and taste.

name: Bill McBay
snippet: What can you say about The Keg that hasn’t already been said? I will start by pointing out that the smiles and personality of the hosts and servers that are always a part of a Keg visit, still shine right through the masks everyone still has to wear. Our server, Eva M was awesome. Very attentive and super friendly. Nailed everything and still kept coming back to check on us even as the restaurant started to fill at an alarming rate. What a great way to start an evening that ended with Genesis on a big stage. We will be back for sure. If you get a chance to book a table beside the huge fireplace, do it. So cozy.

name: laya shokravi
snippet: been a customer since 2017. 5/5 food and good service. strongly recommend calamari and mushroom neptune for appetizer, peppercorn steak and lobster tail with a side of mushroom risotto or mashed potato from their main course menu and brownie for dessert. their food has been consistent for 5 yrs, which i value. the thing about keg is that u shouldn't go there to get a salad and chicken breast, get the steak or lobster and something you haven't tried from their appetizer menu, don't go for what u can get from other places! for drink, i recommend the mango chilli or is it called mango jalapeño something.

name: Grace Hong
snippet: I ordered a classic new york strip, medium rare. It camed as a little bit overcooked, but it was pretty good though. Ordering classic ones, you will have a warm bread, a salad, and main dish with a side dish such as baked potato. Good location for date night!

name: Anton Pinchuk
snippet: Got a biggest steak they have. Regular people can share, but I had all by myself. Tastes nice, like a steak I cook at home. Do they use electronical grill?

name: Sabrina Chan
snippet: This is the Keg location I go to on a fairly regular basis. Most Torontonians have been to a Keg at least once. The food is delicious, it's reasonably priced and the service is consistently great. The Billy Miner pie is a must have so leave room for dessert. At this particular location I have to call out our server Jackson. He was just wonderful. Great personality, attentive without being intrusive. Everyone from the doorman, to the hostess, to the people bringing our food were great, but I do feel I need to call out Jackson for making the evening delightful.

name: Vân Khanh Nguyễn
snippet: My first time coming here and I gotta say that its so much better than I expected. The warm atmosphere, great foods and good service are what I get today. Eva (or Iva 😂) did really good service for us today, she is attentive and nice, thanks Eva. Highly recommend steak with lobster combo and calamari. Will definitely be back

name: Alice Lee
snippet: You know what to expect at the Keg. Great service, great food. The steak was perfectly cooked with a sear on the outside, perfectly seasoned and perfectly medium rare as requested. I give the steak a 11 out of 10. The mini brownie was just the right size and not too sweet. I took a star off due to the noise level, it was so loud, almost unbearable.

name: Victor Leung
snippet: What a wonderful time at this location. Staff were professional from the hostess to the wait staff. The place is one with the more modern decor with a great space in both bar and dining room. We were quickly seated in the dining room after confirming our reservations. The waiter was nice and accommodating with recommendations. He brought us our drinks as well as bread before we ordered our mains. All of us received our meals about the same time but mine came out to be rare instead of blue. Although I had trouble finding our waiter, he quickly resolved the issue but taking my steak and told me that the kitchen will make it right. He kept the sides so I could munch on but took my fork where i had to grab a new set from the empty table next to us. When the new steak finally came, it was cooked right plus all the sides including the shrimp and scallop that was part of my order. To my surprise, the manager was the one who served my new plate as well as mentioned that my meal would not be on the bill as I had to eat alone since my group finished their meal waiting for me. It was a great gesture that was unexpected. Glad to have this experience as the steaks are reasonably priced for the quality of food and service.

name: C N
snippet: Marvellous! Delicious food, friendly and reliable staff, and super reasonable prices! Had a memorable evening and can’t recommend the keg enough! Thank you guys!

name: Ella Rose
snippet: Recently in Toronto from Denver for business meetings, some of which , were during dinner. A couple of establishments were very poor service but I have to say The Keg was exceptional. This restaurant is all about the customer experience. Our steaks were delicious and perfectly cooked. Will recommend it to our business partners visiting Toronto. Jessica was our server and she was excellent as were the entire staff from the moment you walk in the door. Highly recommend.

name: Diamond Omari - Clarity Investments
snippet: This restaurant is one of the best places on king west. The manager Chris Avis ensures that the restaurant provides top quality service from the minute you book a reservation to the minute you leave. They made my birthday extremely special and we absolutely loved the food. We highly recommend this restaurant and we will definitely be back! Thank you Chris, Megan, Allison, Shavika and Colvin for your amazing service.

name: Shirin Montebare
snippet: Love their patio, love the staff and love the food. So so so good. You can not go wrong with anything as everything will be so good and tasty. Definitely recommend this place

name: Brittany
snippet: My bf and I decided to try the escargot which were stuffed in mushroom caps, garlic, and herbs 🍄🐌 this was my first time trying escargot and the keg had me sold. Absolutely delicious! The service was wonderful as well. We also both got the bacon wrapped filet mignon, a twice baked potato and roasted veggies 🤩 I’ve gotten this meal before & told my bf he NEEDS to try it this time. The filet minion cut like butter! We absolutely loved it. To drink: A beer for him which he really enjoyed & I got the watermelon cosmo 🍉 it was fruity and sweet and tasted like a watermelon jolly rancher 👅 I literally wanted to order like 5 more! It was sooo yummy.

name: Drew
snippet: My wife and I came to Toronto for our anniversary and stopped at the keg for dinner. Food was excellent but the staff were the best we have ever experienced. A special thanks to Yaz and her co-workers for making our dining experience one of the best we have ever experienced. Keep up the excellent work and we will definitely make this our go to dining spot when we come back to Toronto.

name: Lisa Williams
snippet: Great Experience at The Keg King Street Est on Mother's Day 2022 Justin our server made our dining experience a great night out. Two of us had the prime rib and one had a hamburger meal. The prime rib was cooked to perfection, just the way we like it. Our server was very accommodating with our substitutions /preferences. The service was fantastic! Upon overhearing that I love the onion slaw Justin surprised us with an extra whole plate full of it! We will definitely be back.

name: Jessica Brown
snippet: I can't believe I paid $70 for takeout here. Just look at the food portion...from the way it was served especially the fries to the amount you're getting, it's not worth it! I remember ordering the same meal in-store and getting so much food a plate. You guys should treat take-outters the same as those who eat inside as well. Never again! Steak was good a usual.

name: Tai Kim
snippet: Great food by ppl who know how to cook steaks perfectly

name: NoobSniper
snippet: Went to have a nice anniversary dinner with my fiancée at the King West Keg and the service was phenomenal! Huge thank you to the staff, who were so kind, and a special shoutout to Sarah. She was super friendly, courteous, and went above and beyond for us throughout the night. Food was prepared perfectly and tasted delicious; we will definitely be eating there again in the future. Thank you Sarah for making our night so memorable :)

name: Zaid Haddad
snippet: Had a great experience at the keg tonight. Atmosphere is great on the patio. Our waitress Cellen and manager Bianca were exceptional. They made our anniversary extra special. Will definitely be back!

name: Claymore Marshall
snippet: Solid as any other keg restaurant. Blue cheese crust is a worthy addition to any steak

name: Tamara Taylor
snippet: We were graciously served by a new-to-the-job waitress Justice and she was a sweet angel baby. So attentive and was pretty much holding it down on her own since her colleagues were busy with a party. Great experience !

name: A.
snippet: I love the Keg in general but this location isn't my favorite one. The mashed potatoes still have skin mixed in. The Keg at Yonge-Eg didn't have potato skins in the mash. Secondly, when the waiter asks you "are you celebrating anything today?" and you say yes, they will not tell you that they are bringing you a complimentary ice cream cake. I'm someone who doesn't like surprises and I certainly didn't write down anything on reservation to bring us something special. Next time, I'll keep my mouth shut because the waiter came back with a candle in this ice cream cake and both my partner and I are lactose intolerant. Yikes. Awkward. Steak was good but the Sangria pitcher was sad. No fresh fruit or berries in it; just watered down wine. Not coming back.

name: Aman Bhimani
snippet: Not the best experience. We asked for a drink with our food but we never received the drink at all. They have two vegetarian options on the menu but they were out of stock for one of them. The other vegetarian option on the menu was pretty much tasteless. The “hummus” as part of the dish was barely even hummus, and was super dry. I know at a steakhouse, I shouldn’t expect much for vegetarian, but I was with a party and they should have good service anyways.

name: D R
snippet: Had some the loveliest service ever. Sometimes it’s nice to have an easy steak dinner, and the ambiance is so cozy in this keg haha. Food is just like any other keg, but the service was so lovely it was much appreciated.

name: john luis
snippet: ....only because the surf and turf there seems like they used frozen shrimp. The steak was not as juicy as it was a year ago. But, the service is excellent 👌🏼. Very attentive and accommodating

name: Valavan Manohararajah
snippet: An excellent keg location. Fairly large space and quite a busy spot, but somehow the staff keeps everything chugging along. There is nothing extra beyond what you expect from a standard keg location, but the basics are done very well. We enjoyed an appetizer, two steaks, and a bottle of wine. They also have some difficult to find ontario wines on the wine list (for ex, Domaine Queylus). It's also a great spot for people watching if you are into that. Given that there is plenty of traffic through this particular Keg, its a great for people watching :)

name: Mariam A
snippet: Great location for team events. The food was all delicious and came pretty quickly after ordering We had our team lunch there (about 14 people). What was not ideal was that the tables were set up as 2 tables of 8 each rather than one giant table which would have been preferred. It was very quiet over lunch so food was quick. Overall, would go again

name: S K S
snippet: I went here for a belated birthday visit with my friend and we had the best experience. All the staff were so friendly and professional and made us feel like honoured guests. They took my food allergies incredibly seriously (celiac, gluten free). The food was delicious! I had the escargot and the creme brulee and prosecco - all I would recommend, all I would get again! The patio was cozy despite the fall weather! It was my first time at this location and I will absolutely be going back! Thank you!

name: Aaliyah Kean
snippet: Went there last night for dinner my waiters name was Jackson he had amazing customer service skills he was like a breath of fresh air the food was amazing but Jackson himself is why I give it 5 stars; I will definitely be asking for him again for my next visit

name: Olena Mayorova
snippet: Very nice place. Best steak I eat withing last couple months. I like their interior design. Food and drinks were good. Good service. Wery clean washroom. Will come back.

name: Ash C
snippet: Always loved coming here for the rib steak. The rib streak has always been $50 and now they have raised it to $58 for the same steak!! What a joke!!!! $8 ?? Like really ?? Service was good steak was over priced!!!

name: L K
snippet: This location has amazing service! I was dining alone. My 1st time in a formal restaurant since March 2020. I was very comfortable and felt safe! COVID compliant seating indoors. Lots of space between you and the other tables. I ordered the Seafood Trio with vegetables. Ahhhmazing! The King Crab was scrumptious! The lobster was perfect! And shrimps were large and perfectly grilled! I also splurged and got the Warm Mediterranean Salad: Roasted cauliflower on a bed of garbanzo bean puree and couscous.

name: Oscar Suazo
snippet: Great food and very good service.

name: drstansky
snippet: Came for dinner with my wife and kid, we were treated like royalty. Extremely friendly and professional staff that were very helpful and knowledgeable. They were very child friendly even though it is pretty clear this place is not the best idea for kids. If you’re looking to take someone out on a nice intimate date, this place should be on the top of your list (if you all like meat)! Thanks for the great experience.

name: Marcus Cole
snippet: This place was awesome! Honestly, going in I thought we might be out of dress code. We didn't look like hobos, but we weren't exactly dressed up. Just jeans, cargo shorts, t-shirt. Never once did they make us feel unwelcome or uncomfortable. Top notch customer service all around. I got the prime rib and my wife got the baked chicken. The prime rib was one of the best I have ever had! My wife really enjoyed the chicken, too. We splurged and got dessert since we're visiting on vacation. We split the fudge brownie Sunday. It was very tasty! Overall, I will definitely be recommending this restaurant to everyone I know!

name: Shelley S.
snippet: Great appies and cocktails! My partner comes for steak frites regularly. Friendly bartenders and attentive hosts. My first time at this location and will definitely be back!

name: Mercedes Taki
snippet: Service was good but the steak was too well done despite asking for medium.Also it was so cold in the dining area inside that the food got cold so fast.

name: Joan Granatstein
snippet: Great space and service. The only complaint I have is that the steaks are not consistent quality. Some times excellent, other times not.

name: Jake S
snippet: Place looks nice, service is sometimes good and sometimes meh, food was tasty.

name: Kitty
snippet: This keg had the best service I have ever experienced. We ordered a lobster tail dinner and it was too salty, their manager told us that salt wasn’t added, he could offer us something different or we could have a new lobster plate. Every single server we have encountered are excellent. However, although we had a new plate of lobster, it was still amazingly salty... but I am so satisfied with the service, from the front desk, our server, and to the manager; they are just excellent. Brad, our server, is fabulous. He is so sincere and enthusiastic; he made us feel very welcomed and comfortable. Brad was the best server I have encountered so long, anyone who has him as employee truly possess a precious asset. We would definitely be here again just for the service.

name: Leonard E
snippet: I'm here with my best friend & his spouse; they're having dinner and I'm tagging along for the ride. This downtown location was busy and there was a 10 minute wait for the dining room. We chose to seat in the bar because we're running late. My beverage of choice tonight is the house Polar Ice Vodka Keg-size for $10.50. It's traditional Keg decor of dark rich colours and low lighting. The music level was average and conversation level was high. Still, it's a nice place and I'll come back for dinner in the future.

name: Chelle B
snippet: The staff here was very accommodating. We had a slightly larger party than normal as we were celebrating both a graduation and a birthday. The two waitresses we had were great, very friendly and kept our waters full constantly which is a small but important thing for us. The food was wonderful everyone was happy and the manager was especially great as she helped to accommodate an allergy and a mistake in orders made. Would recommend this place 100% not only for the food but the staff as well.

name: Kirstie
snippet: Decided to make this location a midway point for the girls get together. I am really not a fan of the Keg especially since my last experience at the Keg Mansion. This time around our server was really nice, attentive and he was funny. He treated all his tables around us the same. The food... the lobster tails and iceberg salad was yummy. I can see myself going back for more to this location! Thank you for the bday memories🤗

name: Michele D.
snippet: This location has quite a large dining and lounge area. While many wait for a table in the dining room, you can seat yourself in the lounge which offers the same menu. It was a lovely dinner last night in the lounge by the fireplace, friendly staff and delicious food!

name: Shirin
snippet: The Keg is my favourite restaurant in Toronto and this location is the best. Everyone there is so kind and accommodating. I go there regularly to do my work and have some wine and they always check on me and ask if I need anything. Really healthy work culture, you can see that everyone gets along quite well. Thanks guys for always making me feel special every time I go. ps. I had one incident where a guy made me feel uncomfortable and they took care of the situation and all of them checked on me, including the GM. They even took care of my bill that day too. Thank you!!

name: Brandon Horsky
snippet: Food was great, service was fantastic from our server. The bartender really struggled to make decent drinks, I'm not sure if he/she was training but that's what dropped the review from 5 stars to 4. Otherwise great place!

name: Joshua Buck
snippet: Great atmosphere, food was delicious. Ben was an excellent server

name: Tiffany Grant
snippet: My husband and I just spent the weekend in Toronto for our 5th wedding anniversary. The plan was to do a little shopping stay in a nice hotel and hit up the keg (our go to date night spot at home). We've never had a bad experience but we've never had an outstanding experience like this. The doormen were extremely friendly, even standing outside in the rain only to hold the door as we walked in, great big smiles (finally after 2 years of being masked it was amazing to see) the hostess seated us promptly, again with a great big smile. The server was incredibly personable, so sweet, talkative and accomodating. It was such a team effort to ensure we were taken care of as the team was so well staffed we had two servers and were checked up on by 2 different managers aswell. My husbands fav fruit is the cherry, so when he realized there was some kind of very different cherry that garnished his whiskey sour, he asked our server what it was, and really topped up BOTH of our next several drinks with these cherries! THEN, to our suprise, we finished our meals and drinks and (my personal fav desert) billy marner pie was dropped off at our table with a happy anniversary card without being asked, prompted nor expected. Best of all, after the 2 hours of dining (and chit chatting) we never once felt pushed to leave so they could fill the table with the next patrons. As parents of 4 children, we get a weekend away once in a VERY blue moon, so the time to sit, chat, enjoy drinks and a nice meal together and just a couple was so needed and so appreciated. The team could have easily brought the cheque in a passive aggressive "your meal is done, now leave" manner and yet never once did we feel that, nor did we abuse it ofcoarse, but it was these small touches that let us reconnect, relax and enjoy a very rare dinner for 2. Thank you Keg King Street!

name: Navi Sidhu
snippet: Came in after canada just qualified for the world cup with some friends and let me tell you what. What an experience we had. We were so fortunate to have landed priiya as our server. She made and an amazing night even better. Her wine and food knowledge were beyond my expectations and the recommendations she made the night even better. Keg you know how lucky you to have her. Anyways this location amazing check them out and if you get priiya as your server you be in good hands my friends. Stay class Toronto.

name: Brianna Vandervelde
snippet: Atmosphere and service was great. Food was thr 4 stars. But great quality steaks for sure. Management always takes care of food served sub par. Highly recommend.

name: Duru Kose
snippet: excellent service and food. strongly recommend prime rib and cheesecake!

name: Thomas Wilder
snippet: There is an prime rib called the Omega thats not on the Menu 24oz. It's huge!...

name: Amy C.
snippet: Friendly staff, great appetizers and happy hour drinks were delicious! The teriyaki tenderloin bites were very tender and the tuna tartare was fresh. Would definitely go back again.

name: Sweetie Baath
snippet: Spacious and very busy but although its busy it does not affect the service. Its timely and the servers are very kind, patient and professional. Food is same as all kegs good, simple and delicious.

name: Ney Lins
snippet: Amazing customer service, impecable food and cocktails, price is on the high end but not crazy expensive.

name: Sean Powell
snippet: The general manager here is one of the nicest people I have ever met in my life. Absolutely fantastic experience. Perfectly cooked Filet Mignon, but the sauce that came with it was very weird. And delicious ice cream/cookie crumble cake!

name: David Gray
snippet: Great service amazing meat, I brought my partner here for their bday and the service was above and beyond. We even got a complimentary slice of ice cream cake. Been here plenty before and will be back again.

name: D A
snippet: Great food and serious service here. Ask for Ben. He’s genuine, informative and very attentive. Keep it up Ben. You’re putting smiles on faces every day you’re in.

name: Haben Iyob
snippet: Drinks were good, food was great and the service was even better. We are a group of 20 people, and service was great and attentive. I got the NY Striploin and it was cooked right and tasted soooo good. Also, I got the Dark and Stormy made with Gosling Rum for $6 (Tuesday special)... can't go wrong with that.

name: Markhus Morgan
snippet: This is a lovely keg An older conversión with modernized cleanliness Perfect service. Decent rates. Reliable steak And great affordable wine selection I find it's pleasing always

name: Ale Fabiani
snippet: You can’t go wrong with The Keg!!!! If you feel like eating a juicy, delicious steak...while having a lovely dinner or lunch, The Keg is your option. No matter the Keg you go to, it is always good. Starting with the bread they bring at the begging that is always warm, the garlic mash potatoes in combination with the delicious steak, will definitely bring you heaven. And, please, order the crémé brûlé for dessert. Always good! Always the Keg!

name: WD
snippet: The Keg King West is your typical mid-high-end steakhouse. It's good - but it lacks the finesse and atmospheric elements of a more luxurious steakhouse.
Easily one of the best burritos i’ve ever eaten. I got the beef bulgogi but made it a burrito instead of a taco. It was absolutely fantastic.

name: Shoval Solo
snippet: Service was fine and the food was good also, but there was a hair in the ketchup dip and the price is too high.And last thing that i didn't liked is that they have pepsi cola.

name: Daniel Finkler
snippet: Always fantastic. Service and food are out of bounds great. Great var staff. Friendly, polite and professional.

name: Jenna Kaplan
snippet: Really great dinner as usual and the staff were so kind and friendly! Really solid location

name: Nick B
snippet: The food was the standard good quality Keg menu. The staff at this location are exceptional.

name: Kim Corcoran
snippet: Family Day 2022 and what an awesome experience. From welcome to goodbye and everything in between! The service was top notch, the food was AMAZING and the atmosphere was so comfortable. Highly recommend this location and I will certainly be back!

name: Marcel Martini
snippet: We often go to different restaurants in all price categories, but this was surely amongst the best experiences I ever had. Nice atmosphere, really high food quality and a very friendly and attentive service (thanks to Stephen) without being to intrusive. Got a free dessert since it was my birthday. Highly recommended

name: Ev Delen
snippet: Fantastic service and delicious steak in a well appointed and thought out atmosphere. Our server, JJ, was attentive, informative, and friendly taking the time to speak casually with us about more than just the meal options and was always there to top up our wine. The food was brilliant, as to be expected from The Keg. Restrooms were clean and taken care of. Only disappointment was the Americano after the meal which tasted burnt, but it was promptly taken away and did not even appear on the bill. Highly recommended!

name: Hwasoo Lee
snippet: I had a great time; the food and service were terrific!

name: Jennifer Ryan
snippet: I enjoy going to the keg ...usually I go to yonge and Lawrence. But this time my friend took me to king st west...it was nice and the steak I had was delicious on a bed of sweet potatoes and pumpkin. With a side of asparagus. My friend had the chicken and ribs ...he found the ribs not melt off the bone with little flavor so was a little disappointed. We skipped desert and coffee...

name: Gianfranco Fuoco
snippet: Very nice steak and good atmosphere

name: Christopher Kennedy
snippet: Honestly it’s not great for the price. The steak was charred on the bottom like the grill had flared up uncontrollably, and the drinks were sickeningly sweet. Service was good although the hosts definitely didn’t know what was going on. I said I didn’t have a reservation and it seemed like they’d never had anyone say that before. Fries were good but sort of a mix between McD’s and Steak and Shake. Nothing special. Dessert was a copy pasted flowerless chocolate brownie. Solid, but unremarkable. However, for $4 it was the best value of the meal. Atmosphere is cool, swanky. But it feels put on when the food doesn’t bring it.

name: Ryan Laljie
snippet: Today I decided I'd take a page out of Leonardo Di Caprio's play book. (If you have the power to eat alone in a restaurant or sit in a cinema hall then you can do anything in life) I decided I would shave, shower, fix myself up and throw on a suit (like batman) but it really didn't matter. I literally called a head. I did not pay a cent here, I believe they learned the errors or their ways. I have purchased my own steak from Rabba that I will season and cook myself. Mr. Di Caprio, I will keep on trying to get there P.S. I know we're all Irish today but The Departed is my favorite Bhastan Movies of all time ya Irish Kant.... lol

name: Mike McMahon
snippet: I have visited this locations several times this year and have never been disappointed with the service or the food. This last visit both my friend and myself ordered the 10oz prime rib. Mine was to be medium rare and my friend asked for rare. I knew that I was not overly hungry and would likely be asking for a take away bag. However, when the dinners arrived, there was a clear size and thickness difference between my 10 oz. Prime Rib and that 10 oz. of my friends. Although i knew the size was more then satisfactory for my immediate hunger needs, i mentioned the difference in size to our server. To her credit within five minutes, the chef was out with a more then adequate make up cut to minimize the difference between the two. Kudos to both server and chef for a quick fix to a "small dinner " problem.

name: John Kruse
snippet: Great atmosphere and great wait staff!! Breanna was our server and she was Amazing! We have been walking all over the city all day in the snow and extremely exhausted and hungry but Breanna our server lifted our spirits and made our dinning experience memorable. We love 💕 Toronto and people like Breanna at The Keg on King street made this dinning experience delightful and memorable.

name: Cadie An
snippet: I visited several locations already and they never failed me for both fine dining experience and excellent customer service. Love it and my mom will too (sure thing).

name: Suja Sri Satgunarajah
snippet: Always an amazing experience at this location. The staff really go above and beyond. Our waitress offered us the three cheese butter for our bread (which is a secret menu option) and it was delicious! The steaks are always cooked to perfection here and their patio is perfect for enjoying the busy yet private feel of a dining out experience

name: Tian Sun
snippet: Great place to hang out with friends. The Meat was good and flavorful. The salad was disappointing (very saggy and the portion was very small).

name: Malak El Shishiny
snippet: So good to be back to indoor dining! Thank you The Keg for making the return such a pleasant experience. Great food, amazing service and just a great all round experience!

name: Stephen Perry
snippet: Absolutely disgusting. Went to this place with valid ID and papercopy including downloaded copy of proof of vaccination. Got told that they are only accepting QR for proof. It killed out night out for Valentine's a day early. If any of you want to start a legal action with me. Please contact me.

name: Yuki T
snippet: The person who made a reservation for us indicated that we were celebrating a birthday. In prior years, we were asked whether we were celebrating any event and were even given cake, which is why we love coming to the Keg! We figured we would be asked about it after dinner, but once our plates were taken away, we were handed the cheque.

name: f c
snippet: This is a default place for meeting up with old friends I haven't seen in awhile. Awesome service and always enjoyed my time here. I have tried the prime rib and top sirloin cuts. Both have been great!

name: Greg Shoup
snippet: Service was great, really went above and beyond to help us celebrate a special occasion!

name: Anika Manohar
snippet: Beautiful restaurant and a gorgeous spot to relax with friends on King St. Chic, modern, and luxe, it's our date night spot.

name: Mary Ann
snippet: My partner and I had our first dinner date here. We are in a long distance relationship and after the Canadian borders opened post pandemic, we were able to meet physically. We chose Toronto as our first destination and on our first night together we walked down King st. Most kitchens were near closing time and The Keg accepted us in while the kitchen was still open. From the minute we arrived, we were rushed. I had to use the restroom and by the time I came out I was rushed to place an order. We sat inside and ordered 2 salmon dinner plates. About half an hour later the waitress came out with 1 plate. She mistakenly thought we ordered 1 plate instead of 2, because she was so rushed to take our order. We left hungry and dissatisfied. The Keg will remain our first date spot, but unfortunately won't be repeated.

name: Dan Douglas
snippet: Booked their "Library" party room to celebrate a wedding and a couple days before they called and told us that we got bumped out of the room for another party that had a couple more people (despite already booking the room with them). Other than that it was like a normal Keg, but service was pretty slow and some of the food sat in the window long enough for it to be cold by the time it got to us. Overall find a different restaurant in Toronto around that area that will care more about your business and experience.

name: Domnia Daniels
snippet: This is our favorite Keg. Excellent food and service. Attention to details from our server Bianca elevated the evening. Always a pleasure ☺️

name: Akrem Faraja
snippet: First time going to this location and the service was amazing. The server Tammarah was kind / friendly. She recommended the cauliflower and it tasted great. Also the dessert cake was to delicious. Will be going back !

name: Matthew Onley
snippet: Solid food and cocktails. Ordered the peppercorn steak and was underwhelmed by the cut of the meat I received, but it was otherwise perfectly cooked and crusted nicely with peppercorn. Standard cocktails - nothing too creative. Overall good experience and affordable drinks. The steak was overpriced for the quality of cut I received.

name: valen jude jambaro
snippet: We decided to come here after work to celebrate post valentines and we loved it. The steak is perfect, just the way I like it and my boyfriend enjoyed his medium rare steak as well. The miner’s pie ice cream is my favourite. Definitely coming back here again.

name: Jason Sawyer
snippet: As always quality control was on point. Food tastes exactly how you expect it to, every time. From seating to getting the check, a sell oiled machine. Still a great value in my opinion

name: Sara Ann Yatim
snippet: Hostess at the door was extremely aggressive and made hand gestures that were rude which I did not appreciate, but we were served by Austin and he made it up with a great service! Drinks and appetizers were so quick and prices were great for a king street location he was so professional and nice, he checked on us regularly and I’ll definitely will be returning because of the experience he provided.

name: Christopher Berwick
snippet: The best food and service I've ever had. The bacon wrapped steak with blue cheese was better than the Brazilian bbqs in Toronto. Just incredible.

name: Gleb Sivitsky
snippet: Consistent, good quality steak for the price. The decor is very chic

name: Alex Ngo
snippet: Updating my previous review where I had bad luck with overcooked ribs several months ago. The manager reached out to me to apologize and encouraged me to try the restaurant again. I got the ribs again and this time they were amazing. They were soft enough that I could separate the bones from the meat with a spoon (no knife needed). Quite pleased with the experience this time

name: Daryl Quek
snippet: Tasty prime rib at a great price. Plenty of options for different cuts of meat and drinks.

name: Arsham G
snippet: If you’re looking for mid-market hotel lobby vibes and steak cooked worse than you can do at home, go here.

name: Will Weitendorf
snippet: Very friendly and efficient host and server. Beautiful ambiance and delicious food. Lovely dining experience, as always.

name: masterhand services
snippet: Our group was served by one of the most attentive and kindest server we have ever experienced - kudos to Nicole for showing us true Keg hospitality!Aside from the amazing service, the food was delicious.Love this location!

name: Iskie Isketerol
snippet: Great location in downtown Toronto. The roaring fire is great on a cold winter night. The Prime Rib is a good value and a favorite choice. Veggies were a trifle overdone but ok

name: Fabian Heer
snippet: Always a great place for food, fancy drinks and the waitresses are always good looking and nice 😉

name: L W
snippet: The manager Chris is the best! We have had a bad experience with the takeout before but he helped my bf with the last takeout and the steak is well done. Both of us really appreciate his help. Definitely recommend this restaurant cuz they have amazing staff!

name: Avril “Songbird Avril”
snippet: Beautiful atmosphere, the food was extremely flavorful!

name: Emma
snippet: Had a great dinner on the patio with my fiancé. The flavour of the sirloin was amazing. We loved the drinks, especially the watermelon cosmo. Overall great food and great atmosphere.

name: A B
snippet: It's a keg. Same as any other keg. It has nice seating outside.

name: Nile Jajo
snippet: I usually love the keg, but honestly this location was absolutely disappointing. After I found out that this is a corporate headquarter restaurant, I was even more disappointed. The food took an extra 15 minutes to come out, after they said it will take 25-35 minutes to be ready. I ordered take out, and it came with no napkins, utensils, or anything. It was cold food, and my stake was cooked well done when I asked for medium. The other meal was suppose to be vegetarian, but came with bacon bits. Not sure if the manager/ chef wasn't working that day, but what a horrible experience. I recommend other keg locations, but definitely not this one. 👎

name: Paige Sabedra
snippet: Delicious steak dinner and appetizers ! Friendly staff.

name: Evangeline Dalaya
snippet: If you want a delicious meal in a cozy setting with good service this is the Keg for you. It's a go to for my friends and I.

name: Fareeda Juman (Shelly)
snippet: Love the keg. Been dinning at the keg for over 15 years and I must say when we go to any keg in Toronto or Niagara falls we always have a great time. The food is always yummy. My steak is always cooked to perfection and the staff are always accommodating so friendly and they love to chat and make us feel good. Thank you to a the staff at the keg.

name: Angela Qarizadha
snippet: My friend and I went to the Keg King West for her birthday and we were extremely impressed by the service. They display professionalism and customer service excelleance from the minute you book the reservation to the minutes you leave. Thank you Chris, Megan, Allison, Shavika and Colvin for your amazing service. We will definitely be back!

name: Rifat Mannan
snippet: We went there for our 2 year anniversary. The staff was extremely helpful and we had a great time. The atmosphere was amazing and the food was incredible. Our waiter was very accommodating and friendly. At the end of our dinner, the manager came by and gave us a complimentary dessert after he found out we were celebrating our anniversary. It was very nice of the staff and the restaurant to extend that gesture for us. I would highly recommend this restaurant for anyone celebrating special occasion or even casual dining. Kudos keg, You've nailed it!

name: Danny Russel
snippet: Friendly staff, tasty food, and good atmosphere. Took longer then expected for our food to arrive. Good service overall, enjoyed my meal.

name: A M
snippet: Awesome service and tasty!!! The starting bread is so good, the cocktails were amazing and the salmon meal was perfect! Mushroom cap app was also great !!!!!!!!!

name: Megan Esteban
snippet: Always come here for my friend’s birthday and it’s amazing every single time! I love the atmosphere and the staff here. They always make sure you have an amazing experience!

name: Helen Stamatopoulos
snippet: One of our favorite restaurants. Food was incredible as always. Staff are amazing. Soo kind and welcoming. Highly recommend.

name: Jeff Smith
snippet: This is a very large, well decorated, great ambience restaurant. Took my family of 5, to celebrate a birthday at 5pm on a Sunday in late December. Seating was comfortable and close to one of several fireplaces with twinkling lights. Bar selection was excellent and quick. All Service was prompt, attentive and very accommodating for all including the 9 month old baby in our group. Beef, as expected at any Keg, was cooked to perfection and delicious. I recommend this Keg for special occasions. Pricing is high but reasonable when compared to other steak and seafood brands.

name: Jaskarn Singh Hundal
snippet: Horrible staff and management. They assess you based on your clothes. Over the phone they told us to come in. When we arrived my buddy was a little casually dressed and they sat other people and told us they aren't seating anyone else. This location is a joke. Because the manager didn't even come out they just sent someone to basically ask us to leave.

name: AFR
snippet: I used to love The Keg. But for the past few visits, I have noticed they put so much salt on the steak that you can barely eat it. I've asked the waiters on multiple visits to go easy on the salt, but no luck. Both the steaks and prime rib are drenched in brine, to the point that you taste nothing else. Great place for a drink at the bar, and great service from staff. But I won't be eating there again until they get the fact that I am not there for salt and butter. I am there to taste the food as it should be.

name: Osha Honey
snippet: Comfortable atmosphere; service fluctuates with regard to timing and infrequency of attendance. Enjoyable steak. Crab legs too soft to snap; served questionably with a cocktail sauce. Seating needs thorough vacuuming. Overall: a cozy comfortable space with enjoyable food and relatively helpful staff.

name: Syd Fernandez
snippet: Our company hosted our Christmas dinner here and I was greatly impressed. Like all other Kegs, the food is excellent. Perfectly cooked steaks, wonderful mixed drinks and friendly attentive staff. We had two servers for our table of 8 who were simple incredible. Thank you for the great evening, staff of the Keg. Thoroughly enjoyed the evening.

name: Ricky Liorti
snippet: The Keg on King St is great. Nice environment and the food, like at all Kegs, is amazing. Service was great and pricing is very fair for the kind and amount of food you get. Only kind of negative thing I can say is that the booths are a bit small. We were four men and were a bit tight, but luckily they’re was space at a bigger table so we just moved over. Definitely recommend coming to check it out.

name: Kevin Eh
snippet: Front staff and server were great. First time to this Keg but have been to other location many times and have always had a great experience and great food. I had the baseball steak (as usual), it was burnt on the outside but cooked to the right tempature. When I flagged the server he agreed and brought it back. Second round it was still chard on the edges but not enough to complain as it was there second go at it and I wanted to eat. Will go back to the Keg, but maybe not this location.

name: Amandeep Randhawa
snippet: Been to The Keg 100+ times and I've never experienced my food this way. Steak over cooked, terrible presentation of the food, my gf's burger came with the top portion falls off, many signature items not available, ordered an espresso, cold and about 1/3 of it on my plate and napkin. Very disappointing especially after looking forward to a meal there for months.

name: Mélissa Munroe
snippet: This keg restaurant is predictably very good. The customer service is second to none and their menu is perfect for any meat lover. It also has a beautiful Decour and their hot bread with butter is a great start to any meal. I always leave very pleased with each part of the experience. Highly recommend it.

name: Noway Namish
snippet: I eat at the Keg all the time; like every couple of weeks. Was worried that Cara Foods would change the quality of the food and that has now happened! The sirloin was grisly and thin. It reminded me of the old Ponderosa steaks. I also loved the old onion frizzles. They now are factory made and are so salty there are inedible! Such a shame that Cara decided to squeeze out extra profit for it's shareholders by reducing the food quality and still charge the same price. I miss the old Ked (pre-Covid and pre-Cara).

name: Bhavini Patel
snippet: To begin with, I would like to thank our server Vito - he was serving us at the patio on a very hot evening. I have dietary restrictions and allergies and he made sure my needs were met. Unfortunately during our time at the patio there was a downpour and ultimately all guests had to be redirected back in. As this was mother nature's doing, we had no concerns, can't predict the weather. But this brings me to our encounter with the evening manager Chad - what a great manager and human being. Once we were relocated, Chad came to our table to make sure our dinner needs were met - all was fine. But he went above and beyond when it came time to pay our bill. It was a very busy evening at The Keg and I am sure the kitchen was working hard to have meals out in a timely fashion. Chad took the extra step and took care of our apps and offered us dessert. We declined the dessert so he offered dessert to go. We were so taken aback as we haven't experienced such great customer service ever! He made us feel real good about our experience and made sure we were taken care of. All managers/staff to be should be trained by Chad as he knows how to provide exceptional customer service. We would like to extend our gratitude out to Chad and the team of King West who clearly work really hard to make sure their customers walk away feeling real good. And food, delicious as always! Thank you!!

name: chris dupuis
snippet: Never disappoints, amazing steak, great sides, quick and friendly service. The only complaint is that the sangria always tastes different (ordered 4+ times and never has tasted the same), sometimes it's really good and sometimes not so much.

name: Ian Turner
snippet: Always a great time and meal. My steak was cooked to absolute perfection, very juicy and tender.

name: Nick Di Paola
snippet: Always great to be at the Keg on King West. You know you’re getting a nice atmosphere and a great steak.

name: Mario Roma
snippet: A real off the beaten path steakhouse. Downtown Toronto and easily missed. This location has a great personal touch to it. Seating selection for your every mood. Up front and center, in the crowd or quiet and personal. It’s all available. Food is great and portions are generous. Parking could be challenging depending on what day and time but the experience will make up for it.

name: Dillion C
snippet: Meh. Just okay. Interiors are really nice but the food is just okay.

name: Ryan Tiwari
snippet: I went here for my Bachelor party. The service was delightful. I had a group of six guys and we had ample seating. The interior lighting was cozy and the food was delicious. The best part was, at the end of dinner, they came back with complimentary dessert! I will definitely done here again, and recommend anyone else to as well. Five stars!

name: Randy Anderson
snippet: I took my partner here for her birthday. Very friendly staff and amazing food options. The general manager hand delivered and scrumptious slice of cake and wished my Girlfriend a happy birthday. I was very pleased with the service. Highly recommend this location!

name: O Chea
snippet: I love the Keg and I go to this location often. I usual sit in the dining room and have Sebastian as our server. Even when he's busy he still gives good service, does his checks. I went in the lounge once and service wasn't as attentive which was disappointing. I saw our server catering to another table way more and we hadn't even got first drinks yet, I think in the future I'll stick to the dining room. Food and management were great.

name: James Davidson
snippet: My favorite keg steak house. Located in a fancy part of Toronto it offers a cool atmosphere, outstanding service and of course very tasty streaks! Leaning towards pricey the food is always good and there appetizer are great as well. A nice place for a fancy dinner or date. Cool bar area as well!

name: Luana Nicole
snippet: Omg the specials are fantastic. Had an 8oz surf and turf with shrimp and a side of pan fried gnocchi. So delicious and the perfect portion. (You will need to request an au jus on the side). This was so good l mentioned it to a friend and he took his wife and 2 clients out. They all ordered the same. I hope this is a returned item it was that good. l recommend the bar and and apps at any time. The food quality is always present and the atmosphere is inviting and cozy. It's a great place for entertaining, with a well thought out floor plan. Definitely check it out.

name: Renáta Iváncsy
snippet: The best steak ever. A bit expensive, but it is worth every penny.Great place.

name: Samuel D
snippet: I've never had a bad steak at The Keg. This location is fantastic, giving you options to dine in the dining room, outdoors, or in the bar/lounge. The booths are nice because you get some privacy. For a full meal including drinks, main course and dessert, this is very reasonably priced. My party of two paid approximately $100. I had the top sirloin with a twice baked potato and creme brule for dessert, it did not disappoint. I'll be back again soon and this time I'll sit outside. I made a reservation ahead of time, but it wasn't necessary for a Wednesday night. FYI, air conditioning is on full blast so if you're sitting inside bring something warm.

name: Raddo Raddo
snippet: Went here for father's day. Great national steak chain. Food was fantastic, cooked to perfection. Everything was delicious! Menu is moderate to expensive but staff and food are both amazing! Will definitely come again and would 100 percent recommend if yoh like steak!

name: Anna marie Fisher
snippet: Staff were amazing and accommodating. Food was fantastic !!! . ,

name: Errol Camlioglu
snippet: Ordered the craft Pina colada, keg size. Tasted like watered down coconut water. The warm cauliflower vegetarian dish was ok, overpowered by lemon flavor. Overall less than expected.

name: Kendra Hayslett
snippet: A great time with friends! Sarah was excellent and gave excellent service. The steak was ok and they don't have a traditional Oscar accompaniment but it was still tasty. We had the lobster gratin, many drinks (margaritas!) Plus dessert! I would definitely come back!

name: Wendy Gunnoe
snippet: What I love about the Keg is it's consistent! You know what to expect and they don't disappoint. Three of us went for dinner and had a Striploin covered in mushrooms with asparagus side, small filet with shrimp, and a roast beef classic with garlic mashed. The food was excellent. Service was great. Nice atmosphere. Everyone was pleased. No room for cake unfortunately lol.

name: John Roberts
snippet: What I love about The Keg is you're never disappointed! The Keg on King St is one of the best I've ever been to. They have a great dining area and also a massive bar sitting area which is great if you don't have reservations. The food is always great along with service. You can tell The Keg prides itself in providing an amazing service and I find it sad many establishments still don't understand that.

name: Christine Nelson
snippet: Omg!!! It was such a good evening! Such a great meal. I want another one so bad, steak that is! Oh it was delicious! Can't wait to return! Such an enjoyable meal! I had the 7oz filet. I wish I'd had a bigger one. My son had the peppercorn steak! Yummy yummy! We plan to go back at the end of the month for more! I am so absolutely looking fwd to it! Oh Keg! I love you! The service was also exemplary! Keep it up! Great job! Coming back real soon!

name: Tom S
snippet: I have visited a number of restaurants since the province started reopening for business but the service has been below average almost everywhere. The Keg at 560 King has been a breath of fresh air. I received an exemplary service from the waiter named Stephen M. Stephen seemed to be extremely passionate about his job and definitely happy to be back to work after covid-19 outbreak. Thank you and keep up the great work.

name: Andrea
snippet: Amazing service. More food options would be great.

name: Agnes Switaj
snippet: Elegant restaurant for meat lovers mostly. Not sure if they have any vegetarian options though. I was at Keg's three times during my stay in Canada and I can truly recommend this place for everyone who likes to eat good steaks. Although they had a slight problem with providing fresh vegetables which figure in the menu (they're just cooked) but in my case it didn't really matter because I like vegetables in every version.

name: Siobhan McCausland
snippet: Another great dinner at The Keg! Always consistently good. Perfect birthday meal!

name: Michelle Harding
snippet: Very dissapointed with this location!! Decided to take my son for his first time for his 25th birthday to the keg. Let's just say I did not make him a keg lover :o( Never asked if we celebrating anything special which i am always asked. Drinks took FOREVER then we get to our table our waitress was terrible. Our 2 orders of garlic shrimp were overcooked and shrimp tough, escargot were great, waited half hour after to get our steaks, 1 cooked perfect the other not so much. Sat without drinks and then when we did get a drink it was wrong, waited once again and finally after asking other wait staff our waitress showed up took the drink and then forgot to return with the correct cocktail until reminded. After the long waits and extremely inattentive waitress we didnt dare ask for his birthday cake and went elsewhere. Our waitress was given no tip as we did not feel she deserved and I can't see us returning to this location. Being a person who frequents the keg I have to say the food and service is usually amazing.

name: Hussein Amad
snippet: Our experience was a horrible one and certainly the managers were no help. They knew they are in the wrong and even removed $125 from our bill. We did not ask for and did not want anything for free. We are looking for service that regrettably we did not get from Jeremy or the shift manager. Service Standard has certainly dropped ... Plenty of other options in the city. Spend your money where it counts. H

name: Henry
snippet: Not a good experience. I guess the place was busy for a Sunday dinner. Three of us were seated in the lounge. We had to wait 15 to 20 minutes for everything. Drinks, food, table to be cleared, desert menu. We gave up at the end when it took 20 minutes to be asked if we had decided on desert; we just asked for the bill, which surprisingly came quickly. All the time the were there, not a single manager type of person spoke to us. We saw a few guys in suits hovering around talking to other tables, but nobody approached our table through out the whole night even though it was obvious that things were not going well. Plenty of steak places in the district. We'll be giving other places a try. Never coming back here.

name: Tiffany Bourne
snippet: I went for my bestie birthday. The manager that evening came to ask if we were enjoying our meal! Our server was very sweet and advised us of portion sizes based on what we were ordering so there was no surprises. We were pressed for time based on previous purchased tickets and had to leave before desert, the manager came by apologized even though it wasnt his fault and offered the birthday girl a rain check on her birthday desert. I will be going back, doors were opened for us (not because we were special) but because this is the service you get from start to finish. Awesome welcoming vibe!

name: Amy L.
snippet: I have been to this location several times and always had a lovely experience. Food is always consistently delicious. Too bad we cannot dine in at this time but looking forward to going there once they open their doors for indoor dining.

name: julia nicastro
snippet: Great experience! Nicole B was a fantastic server, extremely attentive and kind. Will definitely be back and hope to have her again.

name: Joseph Maatouk
snippet: Relaxed ambience, attentive staff. Steak as they should be. All our cuts were of a high grade and perfectly cooked, from medium rare to medium well. Wide selection of wines. Bar staff were accommodating with wine tasting until we found the perfect drop to pair with our different cuts.

name: Galawej HB
snippet: Unlike other restaurants, we were charged for the Birthday cake which was surprising for us, and some other customers mention promotion, we did not receive any. We have been to other restaurants for my previous birthdays and the Birthday cake comes as a complimentary. The food was good, we enjoyed it.

name: Xerxes Yoga
snippet: I have dined here several times. Food and service not consistent and I prefer other keg s. Vibe is nice. ( I end up sending my food back several times in this location and few times actually send the food back 2 times here!) Bar staff are good however.

name: Catherine Armstrong
snippet: The staff are so friendly and attentive. My date wasn't very nice but the waitress was sooo kind. I apologized and made sure to leave extra tip. She deserves an award for putting up with him. The food was really good, exactly what you'd expect from the Keg. Really nice atmosphere. Great for groups or dates - just maybe vette your date before you go to make sure he's not a jerk.

name: Andre Blanchet
snippet: The 25$ hanger steak was good portion size for late dinner bite. The gnocchi on the dish were burnt. The server tried to explain to me they were seared on one side. I'm a chef, not an idiot. They were black and burnt. Also, cook temp was not good on it. Will not return. Disappointed as I don't frequent the Keg often, but hear great things like "consistent, you know what you're getting." I hope you don't always get burnt gnocchi and excuses.

name: Jack Giannone
snippet: Keg is a good reliable steakhouse. I find the service to be really good. We went with a bunch of friends once. We all got our food accept two people (I think they forgot) but they made it right by comping our entire meal and threw in dessert.

name: Daniel Silva
snippet: Yesterday I ordered a Keg Classic that comes with Caeser Salad. The lettuce was clearly leftover. The leaves looked brown and necroti and you could feel that they tried to hide that with the dressing. I did not even eat half of salad. The service was bad. The waitress was clearly in a bad day, which is fine. But it was very unkind of her to bring the bill before we asked for it. That has never happen to me in any other place. I'll never come back. Just not worth my money, and maybe not worth yours.

name: Joey Em
snippet: Excellent service, and food. I had the 10 prime rib with garlic mash potatoes, and fresh mushrooms and green beans. The meat was made exactly the way I like it, medium well. I also had iceberg wedge salad with bluecheese and bacon bits, very refreshing. I had had Mondavi white wine. Total cost of meal including a $10.00 tip for suburb service was $68.00 for one! Well worth the money!

name: Matt Kuris
snippet: Steak was cooked perfectly. Staff was especially courteous. I was wearing a hoodie, Jean's and convers and was still treated like royalty. Our server (Sarah) was a super star, untra professional and attentive. Door men were also on point. Whoever manages this location runs a tight ship. 100% I'll come back and thank you!

name: Mike Olsen
snippet: Tonight my wife and I celebrated our anniversary at the keg. The experience was below keg standard in comparison with multiple past experiences. Specifically there was a miscommunication with our order and my steak was over cooked. I let my waiter know immediately upon discovery. He gladly replaced my steak and notified his manager. The manager named Nick, provided my wife and I with a customer service gesture and the steak cooked to my liking. I have to say this is why I will continue to be a keg customer. They made a bad experience into a great experience, so thanks!

name: Baba Dennoosh
snippet: never again. i reserved for a party of 18. only 3 of us showed up because everyone else had better things to do. they wouldn't allows us to keep the other 15 empty seats because "they had other customers waiting". anyways, it gets worse. after 1 hour of sitting down we were told that we had to either order something or leave. i explained that we had brought our own food and we just wanted to a place to hang out for a few more hours. they weren't understanding at all. I asked if we could have extras that people didn't finish and they just rudely rolled their eyes. after a few hours of back and forth we decided to take our business elsewhere.

name: Richard C
snippet: Great service, great location, great atmosphere and great food.If you have not been to this location. It's definitely worth checking out.

name: Rob T
snippet: Overall, very nice place to go for dinner on King St. Cool atmosphere, great service. However, have to warn people the lobster is super bunk. Ordered the steak + lobster combo and while I'm a not a regular lobster eater, this lobster seemed super bunk, it was rubbery and seemed like really low quality meat. Other than that it was a good chill

name: Faris Khaled
snippet: You know when you're going to the Keg you're going to get an epic steak cooked to consistent perfection. Biggest bank for your buck and tastiest steaks in town. Always will be coming back. This place is a pure gem and the service is always 100. Everything's good on the menu, so you'll never be disappointed

name: Shai La
snippet: I can only eat gluten free so I took my husband here on our 10th anniversary back in November. I wish I could remember our server's name. He had long hair. He was very kind about my dietary restrictions and very attentive. I get very anxious eating out because I cannot afford to get glutened so I was grateful that he did not judge me or get annoyed at being asked multiple questions. Food is obviously delicious

name: Jo Go
snippet: I've gone twice to this King Street West location in 2015 and I can say the food, service, and ambiance is consistently good. The lobster, king crab, and steaks are all winners, and so are all of the appetizers. The ice cream cake is great too. Make a reservation if you plan on going, but the best area to be in is the bar seating area. For some reason they can't guarantee reservations there however.

name: M K
snippet: I have been to this location several times and always had a great experience. The food and service is remarkable. I had a small issue last week non related to the food or staff and the general manager Angie quickly helped us out. Thanks again!

name: Iva Guedeonova
snippet: Food tastes great,same as always. Ordering online was easy. Order was ready and packed to go when I got there at assigned time.Only problem, no phone number access. Ordering is online only.Great over all !

name: Steven Vanheeswyk
snippet: My girlfriend and I went here Sept 7 (tonight) and we both ordered New York Striploin. Both done medium..and they were fantastic, like cutting through butter. We also had a server named Jake, longer blonde hair guy.. He is the best server I have ever encountered. Super friendly, when we asked about different cuts and he explained how the tastes change from cut to cut. This guy was great, made us feel so welcome and attentive.

name: Anthony Ishkhanian
snippet: We enjoyed our night at The Keg but were disappointed with both our mains. The vegetables we're bland and cold, the steaks were overcooked and both baked potatoes were dry and hard as a rock. We eat at the keg a couple of times a year and this was uncommon. We generally expect/get much higher quality when eating here and did not receive that on this visit...

name: Jennah Watson (Snauzeberrie)
snippet: My escargot was absolutle gold!! Seriously to die for!! But My steak was extremely salty, for my taste, and the staff was sooooooooooooooooo nice and understanding. I didn't want to make a big deal (they were very busy) but manager and staff went above and beyond and paid for a couple drinks and dessert. So very, very pleased with this The Keg location!!! Thank you for the pleasant experience.

name: Carson Betz
snippet: Ever since they opened their gorgeous patio, this tends to be our "Go-To" spot when my friends and I want to grab a quick bite & some drinks. It's never crazy loud or super busy & it's the perfect place to people watch ;). I don't think I've ever been disappointed by the food here and it's very rare that the service is slow (usually only when they're clearly understaffed). If you need a place to hang with friends and actually hear one another talk, I'd definitely recommend to head here.

name: Pauline Layus
snippet: Most Definitely the best Keg in the area. I've been to several Keg Locations in the GTA, however this one had, by far, the best atmosphere and the greatest staff yet. I came here for my 21st Birthday Dinner, and we were served right on time. The manager even gave me the warmest birthday wishes with a card and a complimentary slice of mocha ice cream cake (it was to die for). Definitely coming back soon! Thank you King St. Keg!!

name: Justin Edwards
snippet: Whatever I went to the super chain… It was amazing.

name: Stephanie Ting-a-kee
snippet: Great customer service, staff are very friendly and efficient, however slow wait times for food… VERY slow wait times, patio was near empty and we were still waiting on our food for a ridiculously long time.

name: Jay Legue
snippet: Service was friendly and fast. Food was good but the peppercorn NY was a little too salty for my tastes; I will choose a different steak next time I go. Not the cheapest steakhouse as the bill was definitely on the high side.

name: Alex Vincent
snippet: Best location in Toronto for the Keg. So much room and they were very accommodating to our loud party of 10 guys. The prime rib was one of the best I’ve ever had. Would definitely go back!

name: kaustubh kabre
snippet: Always a fun place to go for any special occasion. Have been in different group sizes for ocassions that include a bachelor part, birthday, casual dinners, and the steaks have never disappointed anyone. A martinis night was a memorable one here.

name: zoom ranger
snippet: I would give it 4 stars but for the awkward service. First off..the food was fabulous and a deal for the quality. Salads fresh and bountiful. Steaks great. Crisp fries exceptional. So what is off. The first servers did not know the price of their beers..for which there is no menu. It took 3 tries with 3 servers until they got the price right. The manager came over and apologized. Thanks Scott. There is no bus boy/girl so when the main course came the salad plates where still on the table and we had to remove them so the hot food could be set down. Did I mention that we ordered filet mignon But the knife at the table was not a steak knife. Server or non existent bussers did not prep properly for the meal. Server brought said sharp steak knife after we asked for one. Presentation was beautiful. This new restaurant is a bit dark but first class design I will go back but just in case I will have a steak knife in my bag .

name: Mario Janisz
snippet: Looking at some of these reviews makes me laugh. This is a steak house and no, there will not be a vegetarian, low fat, vegan, gluten free option. Go to a restaurant without the words "steak house" attached to it. That being said, for the dude that was not allowed to play monopoly at the restaurant, I would be bummed to but I don't think any upscale location would allow that. Anyway, I still cant figure out if your sarcasm is epic and deserves a medal or if you were serious. Anyway, it's the Keg. Good steaks and good service.

name: Eugene A.
snippet: Location is great, otherwise service is blah

name: Sean Nathan
snippet: Ugh, I hate to give this 5 stars but my experience was great. Food was god awful BUT that is purely my opinion. I hate the food served at the Keg but that's not to say it's bad. Server was kind, food arrived at a reasonable time, and she didn't end up charging us for some extras we asked for. No reason to give a spot a bad review when you're not a fan of the food.

name: Jasmine Salem
snippet: I love this location. Especially in the summer. Our steak was not cooked to our liking but the manager was kind enough to replace it and our drinks were free. Thats what I call excellent customer service. Thank you to all the staff.

name: Sundeep Balsara
snippet: Went here for dessert. The Billy Miner ice cream cake is a must try

name: Mark McLean
snippet: Solid Keg experience. My off menu 24oz prime rib was perfectly cooked. The service was spot on. Some of the Keg restaurants that I have been too have seen a decline in service. Very pleased with the overall experience at this location.

name: Ross Carrothers
snippet: Seriously get that four cheese butter, it's a secret menu item and you won't regret it. I know the keg is pretty basic, however, they absolutely kill it on their steaks. And it's pretty good value for your meal if you choose to get a keg classic dish. If it's your birthday you get a free piece on ice cream cake and it's bloody delicious!

name: William Harris
snippet: Wanted to try the Keg on King west, as we normally go to the mansion. We weren't disappointed. We were seated quickly in a nice booth off beside the fireplace and drinks were brought just as quickly. It was early on a Sunday evening so the place wasnt too crowded. Food wise I had shrimp cocktail as a starter follwed by steak and lobster ( two 3 oz tails ) with garlic mashed potatoes and finished off with a brownie/ice cream and brandy coffee. My wife starter with French onion soup, Cajun shrimp and sirloin finished with creme brule. Both meals were cooked perfectly and were delicious. Our server was friendly, polite and proficient. She helped make the meal and evening enjoyable. Overall rating of this location, food and staff are 5 stars and we look forward to returning again soon.

name: Katrina Heisz
snippet: This keg has an awesome patio and is a great place for happy hour/ after work drinks. The staff are very friendly & the service is above average. The inside is very dimly lit, which can be a bit of a shock when you are coming from the patio and trying to find the bathroom.

name: Tracey Johnston
snippet: Celebrated my mum's 80th Birthday with family. Staff were very friendly, food was great. The chef coming out to give my mum her cake was a special touch.

name: Andrea Gallo
snippet: I went there yesterday for my 7th Anniversary with my partner, absolutely everything we ordered was delicious and the customer service was Top- Notch. Our server Trisha, was very accommodating, and we even got a free Cheesecake from the manager with a note that said Happy Anniversary from the Keg.

name: Matthew Pearen
snippet: Great customer service. Shoutout to the fantastic GM Angie West

name: Sheree Shannon
snippet: Have to give 5 stars. Sit at the bar for the best service anywhere. Because the servings are so large, my daughter and have found that splitting the steak and an appetizer is plenty. Will return again and again.

name: DJ Kennedy
snippet: The new Keg in King St West has the perfect decor and mood for this hip area. This Keg has all the same great service and food you can expect at the other Kegs coupled with cool lounge vibes that make the place really fit in well with the King West vibe. The prices are right in line with the area and offer a wonderful night out for a date or a group of friends that want to get together and catchup. The management team there have come together real well and always make me feel like I am looked after. Highly recommended +++

name: siiike
snippet: brought my boyfriend here for his bday dinner and the steak he had ordered came out wrong. they took it back and when i came back the side he had ordered all of a sudden had bacon on it (he does not eat bacon and had originally asked them to not put any on) they had to then take his order back again. this whole time i had kept offering my food because i didn’t want to eat mine without his present. by the 3rd time the order came back the steak didn’t look edible and overall just bad, so he declined it. by this point i no longer wanted my meal either. they still had me pay for everything except his steak and my poor boyfriends birthday dinner was ruined and he completely lost his appetite because of it. the keg is typically okay but this location had to definitely be the worst one i’ve ever been to.

name: Taryn Wyatt
snippet: Meh, if I don't stick to what I know is good I am usually disappointed. This time I went for one of the daily specials with tempura shrimp. Could've guessed the tempura would be horrible, not tempura at all and really more like beer batter. Steak is always good but side dishes are sometimes awful, like the time I ordered brussel sprouts and they were greasy and unseasoned.

name: Bartek Shaarani
snippet: Standard Keg, but a nice location. Our steaks were, as one comes to expect from a Keg, very nicely cooked. Also strongly recommend the nachos, oddly enough. Staff was friendly, but I'd avoid the cocktails and stick to wine: our old fashioneds were really poorly constructed and the bourbon sour was watery.

name: Eiann Mascoll
snippet: The food was good, so was the service. They had an excellent selection of wines. I enjoyed the prime rib. The apps were good too. Nice atmosphere and professional service.

name: Mariah Fernandes
snippet: Great food and great service. Justin was amazing.

name: Eric T
snippet: This was my usual spot when I was in the mood for prime rib but our last date night here my girlfriend got really sick from what we assume to be the prawns, this happened in the beginning of December and we complained the next day, took nearly 2 months to get a call back about it and still nothing has been done. Usually great food and service but nearly 2 months has passed and nothing has been addressed and that is not right!

name: Martin Ryalen
snippet: Not the best Keg. As a frequent Keg visiter this is the worst Keg I've been to. I come here because it's close to my work but it's always disappointing. Service is great but the food is sub par. I've tried about 8 different menu options and they are never as good at this location for some reason. All other locations seem to have consistent quality except this one. I would recommend one of the other locations in the city of you want a true Keg experience.

name: Manal Hassan
snippet: They have the best stuff. I like the environment and the food .

name: R Clark
snippet: Fantastic location. Use to get super busy when they were open to patio dining. Strongly reccomend this location.

name: Mitchell McIvor
snippet: Been a few times and always amazing. Steaks are phenomenal and service is always on point.

name: s c
snippet: Love the keg - I still remember my first visit. This location is grest never disappoints. Their twice baked potatoes and escargot are to die for. Hats off to the kitchen staff, not only the grillers but the prepers as well who put together these fantastic meals. I'll be back for more!

name: Veronica Johnson
snippet: Very good food great customer service Josh.j did a great job serving our team .

name: Ashley Reyes
snippet: Great place, met the love of my life here! Staff was amazing, shoutout to Sparky!!!

name: Kaylia Wright
snippet: The ambiance was so romantic! The food was amazing. The servers were attentive but not all up in your business. And my boyfriend proposed!! It was perfect!

name: Tommy Watt
snippet: Disappointing that a steak house couldn't cook steaks right. My wife and I, and the table next to us, all served over cooked steaks. I'm still waiting for the wine list and salt and pepper that I asked the waitress for. Use to be a regular and loved going to The Keg; not sure what has happened to this once fabulous Canadian franchise.

name: Diana Vargas
snippet: Always delicious food and great service

name: Marcus Mend
snippet: It's a Ford not a Cadillac! If you are going out for casual drinks This places patio is a good choice but as far as steak goes It's a mediocre steakhouse. The steaks are just ok, the shrimp in the shrimp cocktail looks like they came from Costco, tiny and no taste.. You can do way better by going to almost any other steakhouse in the downtown area. Hy's, (excellent food and service) Mortons, (constantly delicious with excellent service) or Jacobs (which is delicious but insanely overpriced).

name: Josh Matte
snippet: This is a great place to eat, with friendly staff and good priced drinks. They have a great selection of appetizers and steaks to choose from at a great price. I would recommend eating here while passing through or living in the Toronto area.

name: Marc Donner
snippet: Fun Canadian restaurant/pub. A chain, but feels real. They honor a fellow named Billy Miner, an outlaw in the US and Canada famous, they say, for inventing the phrase, "Hands up!" with a confection called Billy Miner Pie. Friendly service. Tasty hearty food.

name: Janet Yao
snippet: Excellent service !! Foods are great !! We have 7 people and we all enjoyed a very happy dinner. Definitely will go again and more often.

name: Hassan Ashroom
snippet: Most consistent venue ever. We love the keg!!

name: Sarvin Peyman
snippet: I had never had this experience across Canada. Bad service, awful manager, very rude staff I booked a table but when I got there they denied and said we are fully booked I was shocked and offended. It was 11. Pm and every other place was about to close.I really felt sad and disappointed. Fortunately, we found another place around to eat.

name: Micky Butler
snippet: Great food consistently offered in a classic steakhouse setting. Recommend the classic steak and salad offerungs but fish entrees also excellent. Try the mini dessert if full!

name: Steve Formoso
snippet: Service here was top notch, very friendly and attentive. Food was extremely tasty and well cooked. My steak was cooked perfectly medium rare.

name: Paul Monaghan
snippet: I've been to multiple locations, this location twice. Steak was tough both times. Keg is usually a good solid known quantity but this location hasn't lived up to my expectations.

name: Christian Goulet
snippet: Food was very good, as was the service. I was just a little uncomfortable eating on a small table. With four guests at a small table, it gets crowded rapidly. Overall, I was happy with the experience.

name: Patricia Hodge
snippet: The size is big and the price is reasonable. Also, the service is very welcoming and the foods are delicious.

name: Web Drift
snippet: Mostly Great as usual; however the calamari was over cooked - I know it can be a challenge and just wanted to let the kitchen know, so mentioned it - and wow; they comped it and a desert - first rate customer service...

name: amit marocha
snippet: Our experience at the Keg King Street was very delightful. After being seated in the lounge area to catch the raptors game, we were so kindly greeted by Liam. Liam was great, his approach to hospitality is organic and we thoroughly enjoyed our service. Thank you to Liam and the Keg team!

name: Laura I
snippet: Great night out!

name: Oran Dor
snippet: Great menu, good value for your money and wonderful service from the staff.

name: Nikki Hau
snippet: Convenient location and warm atmosphere. Always stop by here for a glass of white or a Billy Miner pie. I've had the manager come by to check on my table many times. Very attentive staff.

name: Scott Jarvis
